Sentencas: The effects of mixed conduction on the open-circuit voltage of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) based on SDC20 were studied in the temperature range of 723-973 K.
Titulo: Effects of mixed conduction on the open-circuit voltage of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on Sm-doped ceria electrolytes

Sentencas: Though the measured OCVs of a test cell using high activity electrodes agreed well with theoretical values calculated using the conductivity data at 973 K, they deviated from the theoretical ones at lower temperatures.
Titulo: Effects of mixed conduction on the open-circuit voltage of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on Sm-doped ceria electrolytes

Sentencas: The OCV was dependent on electrode activity and electrolyte thickness, and it was concluded that overpotential at the electrode/electrolyte interfaces affected the OCV because of internal short circuit.
Titulo: Effects of mixed conduction on the open-circuit voltage of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on Sm-doped ceria electrolytes

Sentencas: The ionic transference number of SDC 20 that is free from the effect of overpotential was obtained using a method derived by Liu et al.
Titulo: Effects of mixed conduction on the open-circuit voltage of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on Sm-doped ceria electrolytes

Sentencas: SDC20 exhibited high ionic transference number with suppressed electronic conduction at low temperatures with highly humidified fuel.
Titulo: Effects of mixed conduction on the open-circuit voltage of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on Sm-doped ceria electrolytes

Sentencas: These results indicate that the electronic conduction of SDC20 can be suppressed at intermediate temperatures with high humidification of fuel, which agreed well with the results from the theoretical consideration of the conductivity data.
Titulo: Effects of mixed conduction on the open-circuit voltage of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on Sm-doped ceria electrolytes
